  "title": "TECHNICIAN (MILITARY VEHICLE)",
  "description": "<p><u><strong>Job Summary</strong></u></p><p>You will inspect, diagnose, and repair mechanical faults in SAF military vehicles to ensure their operational readiness and safety.</p><p><u><strong>Responsibilities</strong></u></p><ul><li>Inspect mechanical components to identify faults and issues in SAF military vehicles</li><li>Test mechanical systems to confirm the presence and nature of faults</li><li>Locate mechanical faults accurately to minimize downtime</li><li>Repair or replace faulty mechanical units to restore vehicle functionality</li><li>Troubleshoot and service SAF military vehicles to maintain operational standards</li></ul><p><strong>Preferred competencies and qualifications</strong></p><ul><li>Knowledge of military vehicles</li><li>NITEC certification in electrical or mechanical fields preferred</li></ul><p><strong>Other Information</strong></p><p>Working time: 7.45AM TO 5.30PM (MONDAY TO THURSDAY) 7.45AM TO 5PM (FRIDAY)</p>",
